Party Manager v5 for MacroQuest
===============================

A complete Party Manager system for EverQuest using MacroQuest, E3 Next, and E9Loot.
Designed for multi-boxing (6-box) with full automation for buffs, resurrection, clicky items,
loot management, and a radial command wheel.

Features
--------

- Party Commander Window – central UI for buff/combat management.
- Radial Command Wheel – quick circular menu around your mouse for rapid party commands.
- Buff/Combat Spellset Switching – one button toggles between buffing mode and combat mode.
- Clicky Item Automation – uses clickies from inventory and equipped slots.
- Resurrection AI – automatically resurrects dead group members.
- Loot Manager Integration – add items under cursor to important loot; assign main looters.
- Dynamic Role Detection – automatically assigns tank, healer, and puller roles.

Installation
------------

1. Download the zip: party_manager_v5.zip
2. Extract into your MacroQuest `lua` folder.
3. Folder structure after extraction:

MacroQuest/
 └─ lua/
     └─ party/
         party.lua
         buff_ai.lua
         click_ai.lua
         rez_ai.lua
         loot_manager.lua
         radial.lua
         README.txt

Usage
-----

Run Party Manager:

/lua run party

This launches the Party Manager UI and activates background AI routines.

Radial Command Wheel:

Bind a hotkey to toggle the radial menu:

/bind alt+r /radial

Radial menu options:

- Buff Mode → load buff spellset and auto-buff party
- Combat Mode → load combat spellset
- Force Rez → resurrect dead party members
- Assist Tank → automatically assist main tank
- Camp Here → sets a camp location
- Loot Manager → open loot manager window
- Add Cursor Loot → add current cursor item to important loot
- Stop Party AI → stops all running routines

Recommended Setup
-----------------

- Create spellsets in-game for combat and buff using:
  /memspellset combat
  /memspellset buff
- Ensure E3 Next and E9Loot are installed and configured.
- Rotate classes as usual: SK, Bard, BST, Rogue, Paladin/Cleric, Druid.

